# Cloudflare Workers Static Assets upload — gitignore-style syntax.
#
# [assets] directory in wrangler.toml is "./" (project root) on purpose, so
# that HTML references like /assets/theme.css resolve correctly (the URL
# path has to match the file's path relative to that directory). But that
# means wrangler's asset scanner would otherwise try to upload every file in
# the whole project as a static asset -- including node_modules, which
# contains platform binaries (workerd.exe, sharp) well over the 25 MiB
# per-file limit. This file excludes everything that isn't meant to be
# served as a static file; the actual Worker code (router.js, lib/, pages/,
# api/, worker/) is bundled separately via esbuild through the `main` entry
# point in wrangler.toml and is unaffected by this list.

node_modules/
.git/
.wrangler/
.wrangler-local-state/
.dev.vars
*.md
schema.sql
wrangler.toml
package.json
package-lock.json
.gitignore
.assetsignore
worker/
lib/
pages/
api/
tests/
router.js
